codex
I found a stronger liquidation issue than the original callback report: the callback is allowed to reenter `depositFor`, and the post-check only requires the borrower to be solvent, not that the advertised debt amounts were repaid. That means a liquidator can seize all collateral, repay only enough debt, redeposit part of the seized collateral back to the borrower, and keep the rest as an uncapped liquidation bonus.
